Class Payment

java.lang.Object
bank.Transaction
bank.Payment
public class Payment extends Transaction
Represents a payment transaction, such as a deposit or withdrawal.

A positive amount represents a deposit (incoming funds), while a negative amount represents a withdrawal (outgoing funds). The calculation applies corresponding incoming or outgoing interest rates.

    • calculate

      public double calculate()
      Calculates the final amount after applying interest.

      For deposits (positive amount): subtract incoming interest.
      For withdrawals (negative amount): add outgoing interest.

      Specified by:

      Returns:
      the adjusted amount after applying interest
